															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/cryogenchaos" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(251810); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=251810&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610227454" alt="CryogenChaos" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=251810)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/cryogenchaos" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(251810); return false;" >CryogenChaos</a></span> <span class="odate time_1349997887 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">11 Oct 2012 23:24</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1586291">
									

<p>I applaud your efforts to make a tale that shys away from the SUPER CRAZY INSANITY that peppers nearly every other tale on the site. Contrast between the fantastic and the mundane is often a great way to create a rich, believable universe.</p>
<p>However, I fear you may have gone too far into the other side of the spectrum. Most of this story is&#8230;well, it's BORING. It's not interesting to read, I had a hard time even keeping focus or finding reasons to care about any of the characters or their fake bets (by the way, the point of the Monopoly money was because they couldn't use real money? Or they didn't want to? Or&#8230;?). The most interesting thing I gathered from this story was that one of the researchers has a daughter and is allowed to see her. That's it.</p>
<p>The intro in particular sets people up for an exploration into the realm of the unusual. Then we get a story about two dudes who frequent the Internet far too often talking about how one sucks at bets in comparison to the other (that's another thing: conversations from people who talk like they're on the internet, as in &quot;Implying I want to recover&quot;, just isn't fun to read).</p>
<p>Finally, I think what bothers me is that you had to EXPLAIN the point of the story to us. Like telling us that it was supposed to be boring makes it any less boring.</p>
<p>It is possible to create interesting stories and characters from noninteresting situations, and maybe the issue here is that the story is so short, but as it stands this just doesn't add anything to the Foundation universe either way. This isn't to say it's not written WELL, as the writing itself is good. It's just the content I'm not enthused with. Overall, no vote from me.</p>
<p>EDIT: Turns out adding a bit more makes the characters more endearing. Seeing them alone with their thoughts and their responsibilities during the day made all the difference. Upvoted.</p>

							</div>

								
